title: Ramen Noodle Salad with Sweet n’ Spicy Shrimp
summary: If you want to add more dairy free and pescatarian recipes to your recipe box, Ramen Noodle Salad with Sweet n’ Spicy Shrimp might be a recipe you should try. This recipe makes 5 servings with 564 calories, 25g of protein, and 33g of fat each. For $2.81 per serving, this recipe covers 24% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. Head to the store and pick up garlic clove, granulated sugar, green onions, and a few other things to make it today. Only a few people really liked this Japanese dish. It works well as a main course. It is brought to you by Lifes Ambrosia. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 35 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 0%. This score is improvable. If you like this recipe, take a look at these similar recipes: Sweet n’ Spicy Shrimp and Ramen Noodle Salad, Spicy Shrimp and Saucy Guacamole Ramen Noodle Bowl, and Spicy Korean Ramen Noodle Soup #pullupachair.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are great choices for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. One wine you could try is Zilliken Rausch Riesling Spatlese. It has 4.6 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 65 dollars.

productMatches.title: Zilliken Rausch Riesling Spatlese
productMatches.description: Fruit driven finesse is marked with a delicate florality in this late-picked Riesling. Notes of vineyard peach, grapefruit, juicy lemon and ripe passion fruit come together on a creamy, concentrated palate rich with melon and candied lemon peel. Stunning exchange of racy acidity and layered sweetness together form a perfectly poised whole. The long, juicy finish and fantastic vintage hint at a beautiful future yet to come.

instructions:
1

Whisk together canola oil, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, sesame seeds, sriracha, sesame oil and garlic. 



2

In a large salad bowl combine crushed ramen noodles, jalapeno, coleslaw mix and green onions. Mix well. Pour dressing over the top and refrigerate for 1 hour. 



3

Meanwhile, make the shrimp. Whisk together oil, sriracha, honey, garlic and rice vinegar. Taste and add salt if desired. Place shrimp in a bowl and pour sriracha honey sauce over the top. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. 



4

When ready, cook shrimp in a skillet over medium heat, until pink and cooked through, about 5 - 6 minutes. Note: Make sure you turn the shrimp often, the sugar in the honey can burn quickly. 



5

Once cooked, toss the shrimp with the salad and serve.

steps.step: Whisk together canola oil, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, sesame seeds, sriracha, sesame oil and garlic.
In a large salad bowl combine crushed ramen noodles, jalapeno, coleslaw mix and green onions.
Pour dressing over the top and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Whisk together oil, sriracha, honey, garlic and rice vinegar. Taste and add salt if desired.
Place shrimp in a bowl and pour sriracha honey sauce over the top. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
When ready, cook shrimp in a skillet over medium heat, until pink and cooked through, about 5 - 6 minutes. Note: Make sure you turn the shrimp often, the sugar in the honey can burn quickly.
Once cooked, toss the shrimp with the salad and serve.
